Dahiru Nyako, elder brother of former Adamawa State governor, Murtala Nyako, who was abducted on Wednesday night, has regained his freedom. SaharaReporters had earlier reported that the 90-year-old was kidnapped in the early hours of Thursday at his residence in Mayo-Belwa town. However, the old man was said to have been released by his captors around 11:00am on Thursday. Spokesperson for the state police command, DSP Suleiman Nguroje, confirmed his release to SaharaReporters on Thursday. 



